  "translations": {
    "en": "of red sapphire, and it has no door pull. As for the Gate of Thanks, it is of white sapphire, it has two gates – between which is a journey of five hundred years – and it noises its yearning, saying: “O Allah! Bring me my people.” I said: Do gates talk?! He said: Yes. The Majestic and Noble will give them the power of speech. As for the Gate of Calamity—. I said: Isn't the Gate of Calamity the same as the Gate of Patience? He said: No. I said: Then what is calamity? He said: Adversity, illnesses, diseases, and leprosy. It is a gate of yellow sapphire and it has one door. How few are those who will enter through it! I said: May Allah have mercy on you. Tell me more and grace me, for I am",
